========,1,preface.
Vegårshei is a municipality in Aust-Agder county, Norway.
It is located in the traditional district of Sørlandet.
The administrative center is the village of Myra.
========,2,General information.
The parish of "Vegaardsheien" was established as a municipality on 1 January 1838 (see formannskapsdistrikt).
The borders of the municipality have not changed since that time.
========,3,Name.
The Old Norse form of the name may have been "Vigisheiðr".
The first element is the genitive case of the name of the lake Vegår (the Norse form, and the meaning, of the name is uncertain).
The last element is "heiðr" which means "heath" or "moor".
========,3,Coat-of-arms.
The coat-of-arms is from modern times.
They were granted on 30 April 1987.
The arms show a fox as a representative of the local wildlife and also for the fox farming in the village.
